snippet.textDisplay:
The Chinese nurse who spoke out about the condition in Wuhan regarding the Coronavirus said that 90,000 people checked into a hospital to see if they caught the disease, the translation was wrong, she didn’t say that 90,000 people are infected. Conspiracy theories do little to help in times like these. The number of infected rose by about hundreds and at most, a thousand people. Don’t make wild assumptions simply because of the thrill you get by doing so.

The main reason why medical staff in Wuhan and nearby provinces are reaching out through social media is so that they can get assistance from more health organizations and more medical supplies such as masks, suits, and even more medical staff. They’re asking for donations, not spreading some conspiracy theory about the “true” nature of the new virus, that somehow it’s way more deadly than the WHO or any government will admit.


https://youtu.be/h8aloXm2NB0
